lenders.name: The Grape
lenders.occupational_info:
In America, home brewing beer has been slowly gaining in popularity since 1978 when federal laws concerning making beer at home changed. By 2013, it was finally legal to brew beer for your own use in every state. Similar to baking, home brewers enjoy the creativity of changing the flavors of a beer to further the experience. Offering spices, grains, hops and other flavorings, The Grape and Granary lets you release your creativity and allows you to adjust each recipe as you see fit. Home beer brewers receive much satisfaction from being able to adjust the ingredients and alter the flavor of the resulting beer.
The Grape and Granary sells the equipment and tools needed for other interesting hobbies, in addition to their beer brewing supplies and wine making gear. For those looking to explore other forms of fermentation, you can find everything you need to make sake (fermented rice), mead (fermented honey), and vinegar here, including books, PDFs, and supplies. Everyone at The Grape and Granary is enthusiastic about their hobby, both at home and work, and they want to share their love of the craft with the world.
